The workflow — step by step:
Stage A: Build the Rulebook (PKB) — 15 files, one at a time
We create each .md file here. You copy it into your PKB/ folder. No code runs yet.
This is pure planning and documentation.
Order matters — we start with vision, then architecture, then standards, then engine-specific rules, then agentic rules last.

<!-- ================================================== -->


Stage B: Setup (Phase 0) — Environment ready
You set up the project folder, install Django, Next.js, PostgreSQL, Docker.

I guide you command by command in PowerShell. One step at a time.

<!-- =============================================================== -->


Stage C: Build Core 5 Engines (Phase 1) — The real work begins
This is where the loop starts:

I generate one file (e.g., models.py for Content Engine)
You copy to VS Code
You run it
You say "Done" or paste any error
We move to next file
Repeat until engine is complete
Then next engine. Same loop.

The 5 core engines in order: Content → Knowledge → Assessment → User State → Analytics

<!-- ============================================================ -->


Stage D: Article Generation + Current Affairs (Phase 2)
Same loop. Now we add GROQ-powered article generation and RSS-based news ingestion.

This is where RAG comes in — content is retrieved, then GenAI generates from it.

<!-- ============================================================ -->

Stage E: Frontend (Phase 3)
Next.js pages. Same one-file-at-a-time loop but in TypeScript/React.

<!-- ============================================================ -->

Stage F: Launch (Phase 4)
Deploy, populate content, go live as public beta.


